They said, pastor, you let me know what time to come

700
00:50:09,040 --> 00:50:12,660
and I'll cut the grass because you can preach, I can't.

701
00:50:12,660 --> 00:50:15,160
You don't need to be out there cutting grass.

702
00:50:15,160 --> 00:50:17,140
I can cut the grass.

703
00:50:17,140 --> 00:50:18,280
Praise the Lord.

704
00:50:18,280 --> 00:50:19,960
Again, I'm not saying that so that somebody

705
00:50:19,960 --> 00:50:21,900
would have that response this morning.

706
00:50:21,900 --> 00:50:25,920
I'm simply saying the early church had a priority on prayer.

707
00:50:25,920 --> 00:50:27,700
The early church understood

708
00:50:27,700 --> 00:50:29,920
that there's an emphasis on prayer.

709
00:50:29,920 --> 00:50:32,220
You'd be amazed.

710
00:50:32,220 --> 00:50:33,880
You'd be amazed.

711
00:50:33,880 --> 00:50:35,720
And I'm not just speaking from my experience.

712
00:50:35,720 --> 00:50:38,220
I'm talking about the experiences of other pastors

713
00:50:38,220 --> 00:50:41,160
that I've been able to have conversations with.

714
00:50:41,160 --> 00:50:44,560
You'd be amazed at how many things

715
00:50:44,560 --> 00:50:47,880
members of churches will ask pastors to be engaged with

716
00:50:47,880 --> 00:50:51,560
that have nothing to do with the ministry of prayer

717
00:50:51,560 --> 00:50:52,640
or the word of God.

718
00:50:55,960 --> 00:50:57,400
The pulpit's weak in praying

719
00:50:58,280 --> 00:51:00,480
because the pastor is looked at as the one

720
00:51:00,480 --> 00:51:03,080
that's responsible for doing X, Y, and Z.

721
00:51:04,080 --> 00:51:05,080
And there's only so much time.

722
00:51:05,080 --> 00:51:05,920
Somebody said this.

723
00:51:05,920 --> 00:51:08,120
I just finished reading a book just last night.

724
00:51:09,120 --> 00:51:11,120
It's the book that I referenced a few weeks ago

725
00:51:11,120 --> 00:51:15,600
that said you must remember that God is omni-everything

726
00:51:15,600 --> 00:51:17,520
and you are omni-nothing.

727
00:51:17,520 --> 00:51:18,760
I love the quote.

728
00:51:19,900 --> 00:51:22,440
Joseph said, you've used that twice in two services.

729
00:51:22,440 --> 00:51:23,720
I like it.

730
00:51:23,720 --> 00:51:25,160
It was a good reminder for me

731
00:51:26,560 --> 00:51:28,160
because I'm omni-nothing.

732
00:51:28,160 --> 00:51:30,720
But here's what the writer went on to say.

733
00:51:30,720 --> 00:51:35,720
We as pastors, we are not an unlimited resource.

734
00:51:37,280 --> 00:51:38,920
We're not.

735
00:51:38,920 --> 00:51:39,760
We're not.

736
00:51:39,760 --> 00:51:40,580
We're not God.

737
00:51:42,000 --> 00:51:44,600
And so the reality is that we look at a passage

738
00:51:44,600 --> 00:51:46,000
of scripture like Acts 12.

739
00:51:46,000 --> 00:51:48,080
Peter's the one that's speaking here

740
00:51:48,080 --> 00:51:49,280
or at least one of them.

741
00:51:49,280 --> 00:51:52,320
He's often the spokesman and we don't know for sure

742
00:51:52,320 --> 00:51:53,840
that he's the one speaking in Acts 6

743
00:51:53,840 --> 00:51:55,520
but it would make sense that he was

744
00:51:55,520 --> 00:51:58,360
as one of the apostles, always the one speaking up

745
00:51:58,360 --> 00:52:01,480
in all the other instances that we have

746
00:52:01,480 --> 00:52:04,720
and we find that he's now the one in prison

747
00:52:04,720 --> 00:52:06,760
but the church is praying.

748
00:52:06,760 --> 00:52:09,760
The church is praying and God works.

749
00:52:10,840 --> 00:52:14,160
This morning I simply asked the question

750
00:52:14,160 --> 00:52:17,640
why and when do we pray?

751
00:52:20,040 --> 00:52:23,120
If we honestly evaluate our lives,

752
00:52:23,120 --> 00:52:25,360
if we evaluate our church,

753
00:52:26,280 --> 00:52:29,160
would it be said of us that we're a praying people,

754
00:52:29,160 --> 00:52:31,720
that we're a praying church?

755
00:52:31,720 --> 00:52:34,920
Do we believe in the power of prayer?

756
00:52:36,120 --> 00:52:37,960
It's one thing for us to walk around

757
00:52:37,960 --> 00:52:40,840
and say I believe in the power of prayer

758
00:52:40,840 --> 00:52:44,320
but our behavior reveals what we really believe.

759
00:52:45,560 --> 00:52:47,400
I know I've said this before and I don't say it

760
00:52:47,400 --> 00:52:50,560
to try to increase the attendance on Wednesdays.

761
00:52:50,560 --> 00:52:52,060
I say it because it's true.

762
00:52:53,060 --> 00:52:55,620
The midweek prayer and Bible study

763
00:52:55,620 --> 00:52:57,380
in our churches in America today

764
00:52:57,380 --> 00:52:59,900
is the least attended service of the week.

765
00:53:01,340 --> 00:53:04,940
That tells us a little bit about what we think about prayer.

766
00:53:04,940 --> 00:53:05,780
Does it not?

767
00:53:07,300 --> 00:53:08,820
Listen, God convicted me

768
00:53:12,860 --> 00:53:14,860
and I hope God would convict all of us

769
00:53:15,900 --> 00:53:17,740
because prayer is so important.

770
00:53:18,580 --> 00:53:23,580
Prayer is so vital and our God hears and answers prayer.

771
00:53:23,580 --> 00:53:26,460
Why and when do we pray?

772
00:53:26,460 --> 00:53:29,340
Is there a pattern of prayer in your life,

773
00:53:29,340 --> 00:53:34,340
in my life, in our church that we're a praying church?

774
00:53:34,340 --> 00:53:37,420
When's the last time we've been astonished

775
00:53:37,420 --> 00:53:42,420
because we've seen God do what only God can do?

776
00:53:43,420 --> 00:53:45,140
We said kind of like Hezekiah.

777
00:53:46,900 --> 00:53:50,300
Lord, here's what they've said.

778
00:53:50,300 --> 00:53:52,140
Laid out the letters before God.

779
00:53:54,260 --> 00:53:55,900
God, it's the truth.

780
00:53:55,900 --> 00:53:57,820
They've done everything that they said they've done

781
00:53:57,820 --> 00:54:01,340
to all the other nations but you're God.

782
00:54:03,260 --> 00:54:08,260
You're God and God worked because Hezekiah prayed.

783
00:54:08,260 --> 00:54:09,100
Let's pray together.

784
00:54:09,100 --> 00:54:10,140
Father, we love you.

785
00:54:11,020 --> 00:54:12,940
Thank you so much for loving us.

786
00:54:14,300 --> 00:54:16,100
I thank you for the privilege of prayer.

787
00:54:16,100 --> 00:54:18,500
I thank you for the power of prayer.

788
00:54:18,500 --> 00:54:22,460
I thank you that the early church was a praying church.

789
00:54:23,540 --> 00:54:27,340
Praying church is made up of praying people.

790
00:54:29,500 --> 00:54:31,740
God, I pray that we'd be a people of prayer.

791
00:54:32,980 --> 00:54:37,100
So often prayer is easy to talk about,

792
00:54:37,100 --> 00:54:40,540
it's easy to sing about, it's easy to preach about

793
00:54:42,260 --> 00:54:43,380
but praying is work.

794
00:54:45,020 --> 00:54:46,780
Distractions can abound.

795
00:54:48,140 --> 00:54:50,420
Busyness can distract us.

796
00:54:52,580 --> 00:54:55,260
God, I pray that you'd help us to be a praying people,

797
00:54:56,740 --> 00:54:58,100
a praying church.

798
00:54:59,020 --> 00:55:01,020
Would you have your will and way in the hearts and lives

799
00:55:01,020 --> 00:55:02,980
of those that are present this morning?

800
00:55:04,220 --> 00:55:06,460
God, do a work in our hearts.

801
00:55:06,500 --> 00:55:08,540
A work that would not soon be forgotten.

802
00:55:11,220 --> 00:55:13,620
A work that would bring forth fruits

803
00:55:15,340 --> 00:55:20,340
because God, prayer is our response to your ability

804
00:55:22,140 --> 00:55:24,140
and we know that you can do everything.

805
00:55:25,500 --> 00:55:28,140
There's nothing too hard for thee.

806
00:55:28,140 --> 00:55:29,660
We commit these moments to you.

807
00:55:29,660 --> 00:55:30,860
Pray that you'd have your will and way

808
00:55:30,860 --> 00:55:32,180
for it's in Christ's name we pray.

809
00:55:32,180 --> 00:55:33,380
Would you stand with me?

810
00:55:34,460 --> 00:55:36,260
I know we don't have the same kind of altar in here

811
00:55:37,100 --> 00:55:38,220
that we do in the other room

812
00:55:38,220 --> 00:55:41,540
but maybe this morning the Lord spoke into your heart

813
00:55:41,540 --> 00:55:43,980
through the preaching of his word,

814
00:55:43,980 --> 00:55:45,820
convicted you at some level.

815
00:55:46,780 --> 00:55:47,940
Kimberly's gonna play.

